CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. B4 reads: "All Friends Were On Hand - The Lincoln Day dinner at Penn-Sheraton Hotel on Tuesday filled the 17th floor ballroom to capacity with Republicans from all over Allegheny County. Pictured above, left to right: Table 30, Mrs. Bertha Rock, Louis J. McTurner, Ola Stanton, Thomas Robinson, Lillie Wright...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Bertha Rock, Louis J. McTurner, Ola Stanton, Thomas Robinson, and Lillie Wright, seated at table 30, in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Lincoln Day dinner
